The General Report Generator (GRG.py) is able to generate reports for MediaHub, KPIs and Student APP Usage,
combining the functionality of the programs: MHR.py, KPI.py and APP.py.

HOW TO USE THE GENERAL REPORT GENERATOR (GRG.py)
STEP-BY-STEP GUIDE

1. Install the latest version of python from your browser or using a terminal / command line

Linux: https://www.python.org/downloads/
          or
       sudo apt-get install python

Windows: https://www.python.org/downloads/
         https://www.tomshardware.com/how-to/install-python-on-windows-10-and-11

Mac: https://www.python.org/downloads/
     https://www.lifewire.com/how-to-install-python-on-mac-4781318

2. Install the latest version of pip, in order to install python packages.
   Copy and paste the following line/s to the terminal. 

Linux:   sudo apt install python3-pip

Windows: curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py

         python get-pip.py

Mac:     curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py

         python3 get-pip.py


3. Install the required python packages: numpy, pandas, openpyxl, xlsxwriter, Jinja2, matplotlib, dataframe_image.
   Copy and paste the following line/s to the terminal. 

Linux:      pip3 install numpy pandas openpyxl xlsxwriter Jinja2 matplotlib dataframe_image

Windows:    pip install numpy pandas openpyxl xlsxwriter Jinja2 matplotlib dataframe_image

Mac:        pip3 install numpy pandas openpyxl xlsxwriter Jinja2 matplotlib dataframe_image


4. Ensure the GRG.py file and the relevant csv file/s (for the type of report you want) are saved in the same folder


5. Open the terminal / command line and type: python3 GRG.py  (python GRG.py for Windows)


6. After answering the prompts, the report/s will be generated in your folder
